description.baseLastPrice: The last price of the underlying equity.
description.baseSymbolType: A Call option gives you the right to buy a stock and a Put option gives you the right to sell a stock.
description.symbolType: A Call option gives you the right to buy a stock and a Put option gives you the right to sell a stock.
description.strikePrice: The price at which the holder of an options can buy (in the case of a call option) or sell (in the case of a put option) the underlying security when the option is exercised.
description.daysToExpiration: The number of days until the option expires.
description.bidPrice: The bid price for the options contract.
description.askPrice: The ask price for the options contract.
description.volume: The total number of shares or contracts traded for the day.
description.openInterest: The total number of open contracts for the previous day that have been traded but not yet liquidated via offsetting trades.
description.openInterestPercentChange: The percent change in the number of option contracts traded but not yet liquidated.
description.delta: Measures the sensitivity of an option's theoretical value to a change in the price of the underlying asset.
description.volatility: Implied Volatility is the estimated volatility of the option strike over the period of the option.
description.hasOptions: The symbol either has options available, or does not.
